const introParagraphs = [
  "Temecula is one of the more interesting service areas we cover. The city has three distinct appliance markets layered on top of each other: the planned communities in Redhawk, Wolf Creek, and Harveston with their newer Samsung and LG appliances; the wine country estates off De Portola and Rancho California Road with Sub-Zero, Wolf, and dedicated wine cellar systems; and a significant vacation rental inventory running appliances at double or triple the normal use rate.",
  "The wine cooler calls alone make Temecula unique. Nowhere else in our Southern California service area do we see this concentration of serious wine collections — dual-zone built-in coolers, freestanding wine refrigerators, and dedicated wine cellar cooling units that maintain 55°F year-round. Most appliance companies treat wine coolers as an afterthought. We treat them the same as a Sub-Zero repair: precise diagnosis, OEM parts, temperature calibration verified before we leave.",
  "The climate here creates a specific failure pattern we see every summer. Temecula runs cool in the morning and hot by afternoon — 30 to 40 degree swings between 6am and 3pm in July. That thermal cycling stresses compressors and condenser coils in ways that flat, steady-temperature climates don't. Appliances that were marginal in spring consistently fail in the first serious heat wave of the year. We see a predictable surge of refrigerator calls starting in late June every year.",
  `We dispatch from our Pasadena branch for Temecula. Same-day coverage across all three ZIP codes — 92590, 92591, 92592. Call <a href="tel:${phoneRaw}">${phone}</a>.`,
];

