    {
      title: "Wine Country Estates — De Portola, Rancho California Rd",
      paragraphs: [
        "The properties off De Portola Road and the rural stretches of Rancho California Road are a different class. These are 3–10 acre estates, often with wine caves or dedicated wine storage, Wolf ranges, Sub-Zero columns, and outdoor kitchens with refrigerators and ice makers. We handle these exactly as we handle Beverly Hills estate work — OEM parts, careful handling, no aftermarket substitutes, verified temperature calibration on wine storage after every repair. The Sub-Zero evaporator fan failures we see in Temecula's inland heat are worth calling out specifically — these motors show wear 20–30% faster than identical units in coastal climates.",
