        "Temecula is one of SoCal's busiest weekend destinations — wine tasting, Old Town, hot air balloons, Pechanga. A significant portion of the residential inventory runs as short-term vacation rentals with high occupancy. Appliances in active vacation rentals run at 3–5x the load of owner-occupied homes. Washers and dryers doing daily loads, refrigerators opened constantly by multiple guests, dishwashers running two or three cycles a day. We see vacation rental appliances needing service years earlier than normal. We work directly with property managers on priority scheduling — if you have a check-in Friday, call us Wednesday and we'll do everything we can to get there Thursday.",
      ]
    },
    {
      title: "Hard Water Throughout Temecula",
      paragraphs: [
        "Riverside County water is consistently high in dissolved minerals — calcium and magnesium levels that accelerate scale buildup in dishwashers, ice makers, and washing machines. The maintenance schedule for Temecula homes mirrors what we recommend in Chino Hills: dishwasher filter every 3 months, refrigerator water filter every 4 months, ice maker descale every 12–18 months. We include descaling as part of every ice maker and dishwasher repair call here.",
      ]
